      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Xandriana</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Word of warning first...pl'ing with a necro is a pita when you are dual-wielding keyboards but can be done.<BR>The best way to do this is to use dark and fear kite so the warrior takes no damage.  Necros can heal but it requires the necro to use mana to heal him/herself and that means possible downtime for the necro to med.  Downtime is to be avoided like the plague when pl'ing for obvious reasons.</P><P>This is how I do it:<BR>I set up at a spot that allows short trips to a pool of mobs but has pathing that keeps the mob from going far when feared (zig-zag pathing is best).  I determine which direction the mob goes when feared and then place my pet a little ways down that path but within pet command range.<BR>I pull the mob to the start of the fear path I want to use and then Fear.  My rogue then proceeds to beat on the mob.<BR>I have all needed commands on one hotkey page to make all this easier, btw.<BR>If fear breaks early, I stand, recast fear, and sit back down (very important to be medding every possible second because dark/fear starts to add up after a while).<BR>Once my rogue has done half damage to the mob, I send in my pet.  This is why the pet needs to be a bit down the path.  If it's right next to you, the mob might be out of it's agro range when you tell it to attack.  By placing the pet down the path a bit, you ensure that even yellow/red mobs will still be in the pet's agro range.<BR>You then let the pet do the rest of the damage and finish off the mob.</P><P>Another method is to root/DoT the mob and then FD right before it dies.  This method requires good knowledge of the mob's hps though because you want the mob to be almost dead when the DoT's wear off.  Otherwise it's a race to see if your warrior or the DoT's finish it off first.<BR>I've tried both methods and I've found the fear-kite method to be the better of the two if you don't have access to non-necro heals.</P><P></P><P>Xandriana Xuileb`Xukuth<BR>Level 54 Teir`Dal Necromancer<BR>Tunare (Krieger)<BR>Wake up...wake up...time to die!</font></td>
      </tr>
