        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Aramancer</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>I posted a fairly long response on this topic a couple of weeks back.</P><P>Basically ST is the key.</P><P>Pull a mob back to your pet, dark, fear, have him beat it down to 25% health, back off, ST, keep it feared while partner kills it.</P><P>Works great with classes that can DD since one or 2 spells will kill the mob and they can sit right down and med for the next pull (about 30 seconds later :) Tanks still need to outdamage your darkness though, so use a weaker darkness or mobs your partner can hit easier.</P><P>Some mobs wipe hate easy (frogloks seemed to forget every time on a single ST).  Goblins seemed to have maybe a 25% hate list wipe resist, so I use 2 STs on them.</P><P>The mob HP update sucks, so when the mob is below 50% visible health, start pulling pet off after every round of attacks until you see the mob health update to keep him from killing it.</P><P> </font></td>
